Stigmella filipendulae is a moth of the family Nepticulidae. It is found from Fennoscandia to the Alps and the Carpathians, and from Ireland to Poland. There is a disjunct population in Greece.
The wingspan is 3–5 millimetres (0.12–0.20 in).The head is ferruginous to dark fuscous. Antennal eyecaps yellow-whitish.The forewings are shining golden-brown, sometimes purplish-tinged ; a pale golden-metallic vertical fascia beyond middle ; apical area beyond this dark purple-fuscous. Hindwings grey. Adults are on wing from July to August and again in September. There are two generations per year.